viz.option:
option = {
  xAxis: {
    type: 'category',
    data: ['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun']
  },
  yAxis: {
    type: 'value'
  },
  series: [
    {
      data: [150, 230, 224, 218, 135, 147, 260],
      type: 'line'
    }
  ]
};

panel.html:

customize you Chart


      ECharts brings you thousands of different options to customize your chart. You can find the documentation here.
      We customize the chart by edit the option string. As mentioned the easiest way might be to use the ECharts example page as an IDE. 

      Let's add a title to our chart, give a name to the xAxis and yAxis, add a toolbox for switch between bar and linechart.
      for doing this we only edit the option string.



add the title:

  title: {
    text: "this is my first EChart in Splunk",
    left: "center",
    textStyle: {
      fontSize: 16
    },
  },

name the xAxis and yAxis:

  xAxis: {
    type: 'category',
    data: ['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun'],
    name: 'day of week'
  },
  yAxis: {
    type: 'value',
    name: 'pieces'
  },


add the toolbox:

  toolbox: {
    show: true,
    feature: {
      magicType: {
        type: ["line", "bar"]
      },
      saveAsImage: {}
    }
  }


which makes the final option string looking like this:


    <option name="visualization_toolbox.hman.option">
option = {
  toolbox: {
    show: true,
    feature: {
      magicType: {
        type: ["line", "bar"]
      },
      saveAsImage: {}
    }
  },
  xAxis: {
    type: 'category',
    data: ['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun'],
    name: 'day of week'
  },
  yAxis: {
    type: 'value',
    name: 'pieces'
  },
  title: {
    text: "this is my first EChart in Splunk",
    left: "center",
    textStyle: {
      fontSize: 16
    },
  },
  series: [
    {
      data: [150, 230, 224, 218, 135, 147, 260],
      type: 'bar'
    }
  ]
};

    </option>


You can also check the sourcecode of this tutorial page. Checkout the chart below. Try to change the chart from bar to linechart by clicking on the toolbox icon in the top right corner of the chart.
You can also export the chart as an image by clicking on the save icon in the toolbox. Cool, right?!

viz.option:
option = {
  toolbox: {
    show: true,
    feature: {
      magicType: {
        type: ["line", "bar"]
      },
      saveAsImage: {}
    }
  },
  xAxis: {
    type: 'category',
    data: ['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun'],
    name: 'day of week'
  },
  yAxis: {
    type: 'value',
    name: 'pieces'
  },
  title: {
    text: "this is my first EChart in Splunk",
    left: "center",
    textStyle: {
      fontSize: 16
    },
  },
  series: [
    {
      data: [150, 230, 224, 218, 135, 147, 260],
      type: 'bar'
    }
  ]
};
